  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objective of the SENIOR study is to establish the efficacy and safety of the
      everolimus eluting stent with a biodegradable abluminal polymer (SYNERGY II) associated with
      a short dual antiplatelet therapy (DAPT) in patients ≥75 years old, suffering from stable
      angina, silent ischemia (1 month DAPT) or acute coronary syndromes (6 months DAPT) related to
      significant coronary artery disease and requiring percutaneous coronary intervention. The
      primary end point is to demonstrate that SYNERGY II in patients ≥75 years old is associated
      with a lower rate of the composite rate of major cardiovascular and cerebrovascular events
      (all-cause death, myocardial infarction, stroke, ischemia-driven target lesion
      revascularization) and a similar risk of stent thrombosis than bare metal stent at one year.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
